    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-16T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.321D1 Advisory Committee/64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-16T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 16, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>808. Department’s 804, September 15, 11 p.m. Department of Agriculture will
                    release to press for afternoon papers of Wednesday, September 17, announcement
                    of decision to make available for export cotton owned by Commodity Credit
                    Corporation. See paragraph C of telegram under reference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
